This course gives an overview of career counselling including the main theoretical approaches in career counselling, information gathering, and decision making.
The laws and research relevant to career counselling is discussed. 
The course supports the development of students' skills of information-gathering, self-analysis, and career planning. It also provides the basic skills required to work in the field of career guidance.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of career counselling and thus prepare people for work in the field of career counselling (career counseling, school psychology, education, social work).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student: Is familiar with career-counsellors' field of work and knows the job-opportunities in the field.  Applies the knowledge about career-counselling theories, career counselling system, laws, and scientific research to analyse the need for counselling; Formulates the preliminary counselling hypothesis; Puts together a preliminary action plan for career planning.
